# Trivy Ignore File — Nanobot
#
# POLICY (established 2026-03-20):
#
# 1. CI uses --ignore-unfixed, so CVEs without available patches do NOT
#    need entries here — they are automatically skipped.
#
# 2. Add entries here ONLY for:
#    (a) FALSE POSITIVES — CVE detected but does not apply to our usage
#    (b) ACCEPTED RISK — fix exists but upgrading would break functionality
#    (c) DISPUTED — CVE is disputed or contested by the maintainer
#
# 3. Every entry MUST include: reason, review date, reviewer.
#
# 4. Review all entries quarterly. Remove entries whose CVE has been
#    fixed or whose package was removed from the image.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # [FALSE_POSITIVE|ACCEPTED_RISK|DISPUTED] reason — reviewed YYYY-MM-DD @reviewer
#
# (Currently empty — unfixed OS CVEs handled by --ignore-unfixed flag,
#  build-tool CVEs eliminated by multi-stage Docker build.)
